OpenSAF 4.2.3 (released 2013-04-15)

    This is a maintenance release. The following items were fixed and/or added:

    * avsv: improve logging (#3083)
    * avsv: treat comp quiesced errs as other errs (#3083)
    * smfd: records correct nodes in SaSmfImageNodes (#3112)
    * avsv: fix some memleaks (#3109)
    * avsv: reset SU failed state after recovery of failed comps (#2919)
    * opensaf: Update AUTHORS file with current maintainers
    * opensaf: Fix build problems with GCC 4.8.0 (#3098)
    * smfsv: change ucs schema to make attributes unique for object create and modify (#3099)
    * tests/safimm: Update immoitest 2 4 to expect ERR_INVALID_PARAM (#3086)
    * immsv: saImmOiImplementerSet returns INVALID_PARAM on interface violation (#3086)
    * opensaf: Update web page and mailing addresses
    * immsv: Providing correct ccbid in completedcallback, when allowing flag to turn setting of ccb-error-string(#3089)
    * leap: fix pthread_create logging (#2971)
    * immsv: Flag to allow ccb-error-string turned on just before callback (#3089)
    * immtools: fix string compare in immcfg and immload (#3076)
    * immtools: add a check for more attribute occurrences in a class and in an object for immcfg and immxml-validate (#3048)
    * immtools: fix admin owner handling in immcfg (#3090)
    * avsv: Correct assignment counters during node lock operation (#3069)
    * avsv: Reset su level error escalation counters after saAmfNodeSuFailOverProb expires (#3056)
    * avsv: stop tol tmr for asgnd dep SI if sponsor SI gets reassgnd (#3057)
    * immsv: implementerSet optimistically sets client node flags (#3072)
    * dtms: log high level node event messages (#2707)
    * smfd: plmExecEnv overrides single step node calculation (3055)
    * mds/tcp : README change as part of #1799
    * avsv : Ignore comp faults during shutting down (#2976)
    * build: Add .hgignore file (#2692)
    * mds/tcp : Fixed gcc 4.6.2 build issues and README change as  part of #1993
    * mds: determine transport protocol dynamically (#1799)
    * mds/tcp:Removed unnecessary bind() in the MDS library (#1993)
    * immsv: class/object-implementerSet avoids ERR_BUSY & aborts ccbs (#2994)
    * avsv: improve susi modify response handling in SG realign state (#2846)
    * avsv: ignore comps in FAILED state at shutdown (#2965)
    * avsv: add failed state file handling (#2965)
    * immsv: abortSync done also on clients in state IMM_SERVER_SYNC_PENDING (#3040)
    * immsv: IMMND Nack's to NID at controlled failure (#3039)
    * avsv: harden avnd_evt_avd_info_su_si_assign_evh (#2921)
    * avsv: fix avnd_comp_csi_remove_done (#2990)
    * avsv: set ALL SI flag when rec SUSI req (#2990)
    * avsv: terminate NPI component when opensaf is stopped (#2978)
    * leap: Abort process when encountering too large file descriptor (#3031)
    * uml: Fix race condition when creating the uml_switch socket (#3025)
    * cpa:Fixed mem leak in saCkptCheckpointWrite() when  multiple vector case(#2960)
    * immsv: Consumed search/accessor is de-allocated by server (#3007)
    * tools/safamf: Return EXIT_FAILURE when pm start fails(#3002)
    * smfsv: finalize search handle to avoid leaks (#3004)
    * avsv: nodefailover handling when sufailover in progress (#2968)
    * smfd: allows campaign objects located at root to be deleted (#2993)
    * tests: fix build problem on ubuntu 12.04 (#2983)
    * ntfsv: Fix for type conversion of float and double when doing encode/decode (#2967)
    * tools/safimm: enable modification of one or more attributes to one or more objects in immcfg (#2950)
    * amf: remove confusing error messages (#2061)
    * avsv: do not checkpoint during role transition from qscd to stdby (#2973)
    * immsv: Convert DN to internal rep in CcbAugment code (#2984)
    * ava: removed cb from TRACE_LEAVE2 stmt in saAmfFinalize (#2981)
    * immsv: fix saImmOmClassDescriptionGet_2 to return the correct size of default value of SaAnyT type attribute (#2979)
    * smfsv: handling of IMM handles for parallell procedures corrected (#2907)
    * smfd: return SA_AIS_ERR_FAILED_OPERATION when poll fail (#2972)
    * immsv: IMM schema is reverted to IMM SAF schema and added support for base64 encoding (#2853)
    * tools/safimm: imm tools support new features developed for OpenSAF 4.3 (#2853)
    * tools/safimm: add SA_IMM_ATTR_CACHED flag when SA_IMM_ATTR_PERSISTENT flag is provided (#2891)
    * immsv: Abort sync kills sync and handles straggler finalizesync (#2964)
    * tools/safamf: add timeout option in amf-adm (#2957)
    * smfsv: all bundle scripts called during upgrade (#2961)
    * avsv: handle component errors more graceful during system shutdown (#2783)
    * avsv: adjust SG attrs at unlock-in of NPI SU (#2860)
    * avsv: init saAmfSGNumPrefInserviceSUs and saAmfSGNumPrefAssignedSUs (#2881)
    * opensaf: corrected variable name of AMF WatchDog process priority/policy in 00-README.conf (#2952)
    * opensaf: remove unwanted macro CHECK_FOR_ROOT_PRIVLEGES in os_defs.c (#2952)
    * tools/safimm: fixed freeing of sqlite_free_table twice in verifyClassPBE(#2949)
    * immsv: Plug memory leak for PRTO delete in PBE (#2927)
    * pyosaf: add argtypes & restypes to AMF & LOG APIs (#2905)
    * avsv: instantiate app SU only in node state PRESENT (#2878)
    * tools/safimm: include <libxml/xmlmemory.h> into imm_dumper.cc (#2674)
    * logsv: Free the resources after processing callback messages in dispatch block (#2910)
    * immsv: Ccb interference check corrected for implementer-set (#2909)
    * avsv: log wrong SU config (#2880)
    * tools/safimm: removed length limitation for create class SQL statement in PBE (#2903)
    * avsv: modified check for deciding SI dependency exists within SU (#2865)
    * smfsv ignore error from saClmFinalize (#2895)
    * tools/immxml:corrected generation of imm.xml when old node name conventions are used for CLM node_names(#2889)
    * immsv:Moving logging info from syslog to trace for PRTO when PBE is disabled(#2886)
    * avsv : Add HA state in assignment failure message(#2852)
    * smfsv: build problems fixed
    * smfsv: improved logging when IMM delete fails (#2785)
    * smfsv: disallow modification/deletion of executing campaign object (#2792)
    * smfsv: avoid krasches when too long DNs are used in campaign (#2805)
    * immsv: adjustEpoch increments continuation when PBE is detached (#2867)
    * smfsv: make suList unique in actedOn processing (#2874)
    * immsv: Correct RDN length check for null termination byte (#2856)
    * immsv: Add constructors where missing in ImmModel.cc (#2863)
    * immsv: finalizeSync must initialize all members of synced CcbInfo (#2539)
    * immsv: allow to assign zero size SaAnyT value (#1538)
    * immsv: included stat.h header file(#2829)
    * immsv: Fix xml2 callback implementation for error and warning (#1742)
    * immsv: IMMD avoids exit when loading fails (#1742)
    * Removed  opensafd  to start at run-level 2 (#2711)

OpenSAF 4.2.2 (released 2012-10-05)

    This is a maintenance release. The following items were fixed and/or added:

    * avsv : Corrected pointer manipulation during susi delete (#2832)
    * Updated README for 4.2.2 with notes on in-service upgradeability
    * avsv: don't send duplicate susi del msg to avnd (#2827)
    * immsv: Fix for 32 bit compilation issue (#2829)
    * avsv:SA_AIS_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED is returned for unsupported recovery actions in saAmfComponentErrorReport (#2112)
    * logsv: discard old messages (#2826)
    * tools/safimm: removed the old xml immdump variant (#2798)
    * immsv: Fix compilation problem for pbe disabled (#2812)
    * avsv : Corrected ptr manipulation while deleting csi (#2820)
    * immsv: Adjust mechanism in immnd for terminating PBE (#2812)
    * immsv: Adjust background mechanism in immnd for invoking cleanup (#2812)
    * immsv: Immediate termination of PBE on parent IMMND down (#2812)
    * immsv: PBE SQLite journaling mode changed to TRUNCATE (#2812)
    * avsv : Respond to IMM when SG becomes stable (#2819)
    * avsv: fix map SU to node algo (#2807)
    * MQsv:Database removal is made consistent for clm-node-event and mqnd-down-events (#2770)
    * clmsv: reject node join request with duplicate node_name (#2369)
    * immsv: saImmOmAccessorGet returns ERR_INVALID_PARAM for empty dn (#2784)
    * immsv: fixed missing 'exiting' word in logs (#2795)
    * tools/safimm: added base64 encoding for non-valid UTF-8 values in xml (#2765)
    * immsv: Restrict values for SaNameT & SaStringT payload attrs (#2765)
    * leap: Add UTF-8 validation functions (#2765)
    * opensaf: remove TIPC bearer disabling (#2758)
    * smfsv: cleanup IPC fds after each campaign execution (#2799)
    * cpsv:kept cluster wide conditions for stop & start ret timer broadcast(#2753)
    * cpsv:deleted duplicate updated of collocated ckpt number sections(#2746)
    * SMF improved error handling at campaign startup (#2790)
    * avsv: set si_dep_state of dependant to NO_DEPENDENCY if si doesnot have assgnmnts (#2771)
    * avsv: set saAmfSGMaxActiveSIsperSU to one(1) for NPI SUs (#2734)
    * clmsv:update standby with SaClmClusterChangesT set to SA_CLM_NODE_NO_CHANGE (#2796)
    * avsv: support 4.2.1 upgrade with preprocessor macro UPGRADE_FROM_4_2_1 (#2720)
    * immsv: change unnecessary logs to traces (#2685)
    * immsv: Prevent corner cases of bad data from imm-client (#2784)
    * immsv: Add tests for some corner cases (#2784)
    * avsv: correct MDS msg version (#2751)
    * mds: use pthread_once instead of constructor to create MDS lock (#2759)
    * mqsv: change faulty LOG_ER category message to TRACE_1 (#2608)
    * glsv: change faulty LOG_ER category message to TRACE_1 (#2762)
    * avsv: bump avd mbcsv ver used to ckpt si_dep_state (#2720)
    * avsv:do not set su readiness state to in-service during admin op unlock-inst on sg/node (#2716)
    * avsv: use per thread EDU_HDLs (#2777)
    * safimm: memory leak in Immdump(#2775)
    * immsv: Use noremal imm-writability check for class-create  (#2754)
    * avsv: update saAmfSIPref*Assignments in standby avd (#2744)
    * uml: add support to start/stop a single node (#2743)
    * uml: use tabs in opensaf script (#2743)
    * immsv: Dont increment ccb->mOpCount for delete of non persistent RTO (#2735)
    * mds: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * immsv: immnd_adjustEpoch retries globalizing epoch change (#2732)
    * plmsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * mqsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * glsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * edsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * cpsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * avsv: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * leap: Replace faulty lock macro with pthread_mutex (#2618)
    * immsv: Remove introduced incorrect osafassert (#2718)
    * immsv: Throttle writes to PBE (#2718)
    * immsv: Admin-owner name added to commit/abort message (#2718)
    * immsv: Pbe renames corrupt imm.db as imm.db.failed_immdump (#2723)
    * tests: Remove gcc 4.6.2 warnings (#2726)
    * immsv: New coord forces new Pbe to use fresh db-file when backloged (#2717)
    * avsv: validate stdby susi before updating dep state (#2669)
    * immsv: PBE dispatch gives termination events priority (#2713)
    * immsv: Fixed CcbObjectModify SA_IMM_ATTR_VALUES_DELETE multi (#2710)
    * avsv: updating preferred assignments field after adjusting assignments (#2513)
    * avsv: move log from mds callback to main (#2706)
    * avsv: read saAmfSUHostedByNode during start of node (#2698)
    * SMF read AMF attributes after RDA role SA_AMF_HA_ACTIV (#2704)
    * Immsv: Addding the modified Imm xsd to opensaf(#2662)
    * tools/safimm:immdump changes for compliance with IMM-XSD-A.01.02(#2662)
    * avsv: Checking whether su is unassigned before setting adm state to Locked in shutdown process (#2682)
    * uml: Update UML to linux 3.4.2 and tipcutils 2.0.2 (#2670)
    * avsv: remove su from oper_list before sg set to stable (#2684)
    * AVSv: Corrected log message for sg unlock-in operation #2675
    * uml: Update busybox to version 1.19.4 (#2374)
    * build: work around new directory restrictions in automake 1.11.2 (#2439)
    * tools/safamf: Added '<Empty>' check for ha_state_val (#2664)
    * avsv: improved SAF logging for CCB and admin ops (#2660)
    * avsv: respond to admin ops when SG is STABLE (#2660)
    * SMF parsing of campaign does not delay swap (#2663)

OpenSAF 4.2.1 (released 2012-05-23)

    This is a maintenance release. The following items were fixed and/or added:

    * AVSv:removed addition of su to su_op_list from su_role_failover #2668
    * AVSv/amfnd: Updating instantiation/Cleanup Timeout for proxied cmp #2661
    * AVSv/amfnd: Sending su level resp when comp restarts during susi modification #2625
    * MDS:TCP : vdest_policy is properly updated in MDS TCP service install & uninstall #2667
    * Immsv: SQLITE_BUSY from start of sqlite loading transaction causes retry (#2658)
    * avnd:use recommended recovery action for quiesced timeout #2335
    * AVSV: Updating the state to quiesced, if fault happens  when SI shutdwn flow is in progress #2648
    * AVSV/amfd: Returning failure if node doesn't exists in DB during NodeGroup creation (#2626)
    * tools/safimm: utility timeout option and TRY_AGAIN handling for immlist (#1012)
    * avsv/avd: return TRYAGAIN for a few more admin ops (#2651)
    * saf/immsv: Add missing include for of unistd.h (#2638)
    * Immsv: All config attributes appended to CcbCreate callback when applier exists (#2630)
    * opensaf: added print message to opensaf_reboot script during reboot of local node - context of (#2609)
    * FM: Avoid failover and reboot local node when standby init is not completed (#2609)
    * tools/safimm: escape quote characters in attribute values before sending to sqlite (#2641)
    * AVSV/amfd: Don't terminate SUs in case of mismatch between PrefInserviceSUs and No Of configured SUs (#2217)
    * AVSV/amfd: During admin lock of sponsor si, deleting stdby susi of only sponsor si (#2553)
    * AVSv/amfd: Ordering comp list in su and csi list in si lexicographically (#2565)
    * MDS: Added handling for out of order of Subscription and Data messages(2611)
    * avsv/avd: instantiate SUs after registration (#2601)
    * AVSv:Performing susi level failover if si dep exists within SU when nodefailvr occurs in REALIGN fsm #2561
    * AVSv:Setting the admin state to Locked state,even if shutdown opr fails #2541
    * Immsv: Support for RTO testing in testprogram `applierÂ´ (#2632)
    * Immsv: Fetch of pure RTAs handles the empty value correctly (#2632)
    * avsv: do not setup references to other objs in su_new (#2635)
    * AVSvL: Added version check for SI Dep state during enc/dec #2540
    * avsv: remove double SG ref in SU and reinit ref in add_to_model (#2635)
    * AVSv: Remove all the assignments of an SI when susi role failover is not possible #2360
    * AVSv:Not allowing si/su/sg admin operations when Tolerance timer is running  #2567
    * clmsv: Initialize track pat node at standby during sequence of node create after a delete (#2226)
    * AVSv: Avoiding amfd crash if controller failover happens during si-swap operation #2559
    * AVSv/avnd: csi remove callbacks to all comps of SU #2552
    * AVSv: Setting the susi->fsm to AVD_SU_SI_STATE_ASGND in su shutdown response #2588
    * AVSv:During failover, if dependent SI which is sponsor too is unassigned then unassign its dependents too #2531
    * AVSv: Checking for a valid standby susi during node failover #2554
    * AVSv:ignoring rank for adding new CSI #2600
    * AVSv: Added checkpoint processing of compcsi #2613
    * Immsv: immdump/PBE avoids abort (core dumping) on error (#2597)
    * glsv: add imm selection object to poll only after saImmOIImplementerSet() succeeds (#2536)
    * edsv: add imm selection object to poll only after saImmOIImplementerSet() succeeds (#2536)
    * clmsv: add imm selection object to poll only after saImmOIImplementerSet() succeeds (#2536)
    * Immsv: SyncRequested flag reverted back to on when failure to send to IMMD (#2617)
    * immsv: imma_oi supports TRY_AGAIN on handle resurrect during sync (#2616)
    * immsv/immnd: handle AMF blocking calls done in separate thread (#1713)
    * immsv/immd: handle AMF blocking calls done in separate thread (#1713)
    * avsv: generate core for amfd when HB tmo is detected
    * avsv: node join/leave related logging improvements
    * avsv: delete PG track info also when node leave via CLM callback (#2592)
    * AVSV: Terminating su after deleting assignments during clm node lock #2353
    * AVSv:deleting assignments if su fault happens during Act transition in si-si dep case #2537
    * immsv: ccbObjectModify avoids interfering with RTA update (#2602)
    * immsv: Admo/search/ccb finalize made sensitive to return code from immnd (#2556)
    * avsv/avd: don't fetch pure runtime attrs from IMM (#2587)
    * immsv: Corrected purging of ccb-request-continuations (#2502)
    * AVSv: removing the assignmemts for entire SU when su_fault happens in sg_realign fsm #2535
    * AVSv/avnd: successful quiesced response for inst or term failed su #2549
    * AVSV: Sending Delete assignment in case std assignment timeout #2533
    * AVSv: Not checkpointing SI_TRANS info before screening for equal distribution in NWay & NPM #2548
    * Immsv:Inform the immnd failure to nid when there is msgno missmatch while syncing(#2504)
    * tools/safimm: Return value verification is added while verifying attribute value type(#2527)
    * tools/safimm: Return value verification is added while verifying attribute value type(#2527)
    * avsv/avnd: allocate more bytes for copy dest (#2583)
    * avsv/avnd: error handling for bad DN in comp register (#2582)
    * AVSV: Marked existing pg record as valid in failover case #2142
    * AVSv: Handling per susi quiesced response in SG Realign state #2530
    * AVSV: Corrected logic to prevserve track flags to avoid overwrite #2035
    * AVSv: handling su fault when role failover from standby to Active fails #2526
    * AVSv:deleting assignmnts if tol_tmr is running for deps during failover #2524
    * fixed compile problems with GCC 4.4.5 introduced in #2303 fix
    * AVSv: fixed comparision check in avd_sg_2n_act_susi #2516
    * AVSv:Fixed comparision issue in avd_sg_2n_act_susi #2522
    * AVSv:removed extra next in for loop #2516
    * avsv/avnd: finalize for unregistered processes (#2011)
    * tools/safimm: harden immcfg input validation (#2303)
    * avsv/avd: white space changes ONLY (see hg diff -wb)
    * avnd: handle op state correctly during term failed(#2376)
    * AvSv: Sending quiesced for all the sponsors in quiesced rsp in SG admin state #2455
    * AVSv: Corrected dependency check when SU faulted in su opr state #2447
    * AVSv: determining the SU state based on assigned susi #2447
    * AVSv:Handling failover in SG admin state and corrected logic in deciding SU state #2447
    * CPSV : Fixed mismatch of open reference count between CPA , CPD & CPND (#2405)
    * AVSv: Sending quiesc role to Sponsor only after receiving quscd response from dependents #2455
    * AVSv: removed spaces in the avd_siDep.c
    * AVSv: Handling role failover in SI Oper state when si-si dep within su is configured #2469
    * AvSv:Handling role failover in SU oper state when si-si dep within SU is configured #2447
    * AvSv:Checkpointing Si Dep state and Impl of Tol timer #2468
    * avsv/avnd: node fail-over implemented (#2290)
    * avsv/avnd: separated node fail and switch over handling (#2290)
    * avsv/avnd: corrected gcc 4.6.1 issue introduced in 3343 (#2490)
    * AVSV: no multiple csi remove callbacks with target_all to same comp #2487
    * Java: Passing state as Act in JNU API incase state is0 in CSI Remove PG callback #2492
    * IMMSV TOOLS: Addind lock and lock-in during cluster downsize #2490
    * AVSV: Rebooting node in case MW director comp quiesced cbk timeout #2441
    * AVSV: Corrected looping logic for Passive Monitoring #2154
    * avsv/avd: don't use freed memory (#2489)
    * avsv/config: default value for SU rank is zero (#2325)
    * avsv/avd: corrected handling of changes to saAmfCompDisableRestart (#2388)
    * avsv/avd: reboot node using node director (#2186)
    * avsv: bug fix unintended assignments (#2488)
    * tools/safimm: utility timeout option and TRY_AGAIN handling for immcfg(#1012)
    * tools/safimm: utility timeout option and TRY_AGAIN handling for immfind(#1012)
    * avsv/avnd: INSTANTIATION-FAILED when no SaAmfNodeSwBundle is found (#2183)
    * avsv/avnd: support ORPHANED(8) in avnd_comp_pres_state_set (#2236)
    * avsv/avnd: default value for saAmfCompTerminateTimeout is comp category dependent (#2482)
    * avsv/avnd: harden avnd_su_si_remove (#2022)
    * avsv/avd: reject decrementing saAmfSIPrefActiveAssignments in steps more than one (#2396)
    * immsv: Better logging by immload when object creation fails (#2486)
    * opensaf: support multiple TIPC bearers (#1948)
    * opensaf: support for TIPC 2.0 (#2438)
    * leap: ncs_os_process_execute_timed use magic exit code 128 (#2474)
    * immsv: Fixed incorrect error log messages in imm_pbe_daemon.cc (#2479)
    * build: undo conditional inclusion of plmc in AC_CONFIG_SUBDIRS
    * avsv/avd: treat zero SI rank as lowest (#2070)
    * avsv/avd: treat zero SU rank as lowest (#2093)
    * avsv/avd: check node and SG admin states at SU unlock (#2436)
    * AVSv: handling pm exit evt when main thread (#2435)
    * avsv/avnd: at shutdown remove CSIs from components before cleanup (#2414)
    * avsv/avnd: introduced macro for shutdown state (#2414)
    * avsv/avnd: introduced global SI list sorted by SI rank (#2414)
    * avsv/avd: don't allow unlocking an SU without components (#2049)
    * avsv/avd: allow deletion of CSI attribute value (#2440)
    * smfsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * ntfsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * mqsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * mds: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * logsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * leap & core: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * immsv: Fixed warnings generated with -Wconversion
    * immsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * glsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * edsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * cpsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * avsv: gcc4.6 changes (#1928)
    * avsv/avnd: fixed type for execution context (#2454)
    * avsv/ava: buffer overflow in ava_mds.c (#2456)
    * logtest: correct test input(#2430)
    * build: agents depend on core (#2464)
    * build: include libopensaf_core in librda (#2464)
    * SMF, no interference in thread termination (#2450)
    * tools/safimm: allow parameter values to contain ":" (#2448)
    * build: only configure plmc when plm is enabled (#2460)
    * immsv: Moved PBE handle close out of signal handler (#2453)
    * immsv: PBE TERM signal-handler & remove imm.db-journal on new imm.db (#2453)
    * immsv: Immnd stop script kills immdump/immload before terminating immnd (#2449)
    * immsv:Reject duplicate attribute assignements (#2412)
    * immsv: purge of syncronous request ignores async admop requests (#2433)
    * immsv: Immnd tries to purge sync request when informed of imma timeout (#2433)
    * immsv: Syncronous timeout in imma informs immnd asyncronously (#2433)
    * immsv: Imma informs immnd of augment-admo with rof==true for augmented creates (#2428)
    * SMFD callback is using correct poll timeout value (#2423)
    * SMFA callback stringToPass correctly terminated (#2429)
    * immsv: Use of ccb-augment handles in wrong context gives error (#2426)


OpenSAF 4.2.0 (released 2012-01-09)

    This version is a major update. The following items were fixed and/or added:

    * AVSV: Ava,Proper handling of invalid csi_name in saAmfProtectionGroupTrack_4 #2136
    * avsv/avnd: added assignment syslogging (#2425)
    * AVSv: Delete PG record node down event #1817
    * AVSv: Sending new assignment when the components gets restarted #2417
    * immsv-doc: README adjusted on admo-release for augmented Ccb (#2422)
    * immsv: ccb-finalize on empty ccb-augment shall not abort original ccb (#2241)
    * avsv/avd: removed last remains of SU si_max_active/si_max_standby (#2418)
    * avsv/avd: reversed calc of saAmfSUPreInstantiable (#2418)
    * OpenSAF AMF model corrected (#2418)
    * avsv/avd: validate saAmfSGMaxActiveSIsperSU/saAmfSGMaxStandbySIsperSU acc to red model (#2418)
    * avsv/avd: corrected 2N assignment alg (#2418)
    * ntfsv: update lib version
    * ntfsv: check return value for pthread_mutex functions(#1453) part4
    * ntfsv: ntfa thread safe variable data (#1453 part3)
    * ntfsv: ntfa thread safe read/send/finalize (#1453 part2)
    * ntfsv: ntfa thread safe subscribe (#1453 part1)
    * AvSv: Allow CSI Attrbutes greater than 255 bytes,#2302
    * uml: added build_testprog cmd to build_uml
